properties.Name: AssetType
properties.Description:
A classification of Asset based upon common characteristics, attributes, or functions.

Ex:
- Land
- Building
- Lease
- Intellectual Property
- Right
- Software
- Furniture
- Computer
- Machinery
- Vehicle
- Investment Property
- Residential Property
- Real Property
- Cash
- Equities
- Treasury bonds

Columns.Name: AssetTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Asset Type.

Columns.Name: AssetTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of an Asset Type.

Columns.Name: AssetTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of an Asset Type.

Columns.Name: GlobalReturnableAssetIdentifier
Columns.Description:
The Global Returnable Asset Identifier (GRAI) was developed by GS1 to be used to identify assets by type. It can also be used to uniquely identify assets by including the serial number. 

The GRAI is used to identify Returnable Transport Items (RTI) such as pallets, roll container, crates. The GRAI identifies the type of returnable asset.

Columns.Name: AssetTypeEmissionFactorUnits
Columns.Description: The asset type emission factor units.

Columns.Name: AssetTypeEmissionFactorUomId
Columns.Description: The asset type emission factor UOM.

Columns.Name: MaintenancePeriodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Maintenance Period.
